{
  "texts": [
    "In the specific example of this mutual entailment (or AARR) reversal curse (Berglund et al., 2023), when asking Chat GPT-4 \"Who is Tom Cruise's mother?, \" Chat GPT-4 replies correctly with \"Tom Cruise's mother is Mary Lee Pfeiffer […]. \"",
    "But when asked in a new chat, \"Who is Mary Lee Pfeiffer's son?\"",
    "Chat GPT-4 incorrectly replies, \"There is not publicly available information about a person named Mary Lee Pfeiffer and her son […]. \"",
    "It then requires further prompting in the same chat for ChatGPT-4 to relate Tom Cruise as Mary Lee Pfeiffer's son.",
    "This demonstrates that LLM (in this case ChatGPT-4) has little notion of assigning its base knowledge as variables with fixed meaning, that can take an arbitrary symbolic value, that is required for logical reasoning."
  ]
}